operators in java-->>>>>>>
-------------------------
1. relational operator
2. logical operator
3. arithmatic operator
4. bitwise operator
5. assignment operator
6.  unary operator
increment operator---->>>>	 
-----------------------------
increment operator use to increase the value of a variable by 1.
ex-->     int x = 5;
    			int y = ++x;   
											x=6, y = 6;

decrement operator-->>
++++++++++++++++++++++++++
the decrement operator use to decrease the value of a variable by 1.
ex-->>     int x = 5
						int y = --x
												x=9, y= 9;

conditional operator-->>
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
conditional operator used when acondition compromise more than one boolean expression .for instant if we want to print a number if it is greater than 2 and less than 5
than we will used conditional operator to combine the 2 operator.

types of operators based on the number of operand-->>
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
there are three type of operator based on the number of operands-
1. unary operator
2. binary operator
3. ternary  operator.

conditional statment -->>
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
conditional statment define conditions that are treu are false and than execute based on whethar or not thecondition is true.

syntex of if else statment-->>
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
int number = 10;
if(number > 0 ) {
System.out.prinln(the number is positive);
}
}else{
System.out.println(the number is not positive);
}

